WEBVTT

00:01.040 --> 00:03.000
Dre: No matter how you grow up,
summer is a season of change,

00:03.000 --> 00:06.710
and this summer was
no different for our family.

00:06.710 --> 00:08.750
Junior moved on
from his gap year...

00:08.750 --> 00:09.880
Junior:
What's good, NYC?

00:09.880 --> 00:12.420
...and was now
out on his own...

00:12.420 --> 00:13.500
What's good, Chi Town?

00:13.500 --> 00:14.540
...managing social media
for Migos.

00:14.540 --> 00:16.000
What's good,
Sam Peterson's Bar Mitzvah?

00:16.000 --> 00:18.750
Jack and Diane
were headed for 8th grade,

00:18.750 --> 00:21.750
so they were finally done
with those school uniforms

00:21.750 --> 00:24.620
that made them look like
tiny black missionaries.

00:24.620 --> 00:27.290
Mm-hmm!

00:27.290 --> 00:28.330
Ooh!

00:28.330 --> 00:29.710
Looking good, Diane.

00:29.710 --> 00:31.170
I didn't ask.
Eh --

00:31.170 --> 00:36.420
Sprinkle in a few
earth-shaking life events...
[ Rumbling ]

00:36.420 --> 00:38.580
Earthquake! Everybody up!

00:38.580 --> 00:40.670
Babe, I'll get the kids!
I'll get the kids!

00:40.670 --> 00:41.750
I'm coming!

00:41.750 --> 00:44.670
Babe, the Clippers
signed Kawhi!

00:44.670 --> 00:46.460
And Paul George!

00:46.460 --> 00:47.790
Ah! Everybody up!

00:47.790 --> 00:49.670
I'll get
the emergency champagne!

00:49.670 --> 00:51.460
♪♪

00:51.460 --> 00:53.460
This is our year!

00:53.460 --> 00:54.750
This is our year!

00:55.250 --> 00:59.500
Yep, the Johnson family was
finally ready to settle down

00:59.500 --> 01:01.250
after a crazy summer.

01:01.250 --> 01:02.790
Pops: Ha-ha!

01:02.790 --> 01:04.000
Great news, y'all!

01:04.000 --> 01:05.000
I'm getting married.

01:05.000 --> 01:05.920
Oh! My God.

01:05.920 --> 01:08.420
What's that you say
about getting married, now?

01:10.750 --> 01:12.750
♪♪

01:12.750 --> 01:13.880
I'm getting married!

01:13.880 --> 01:15.670
What are you talking about,
you're getting married?

01:15.670 --> 01:17.670
I didn't even know
you were seeing anyone.

01:17.670 --> 01:18.670
What are we, friends?

01:18.670 --> 01:20.620
Mom, i-is Pops dying?

01:20.620 --> 01:22.080
Mm, no, sweetheart.
He's fine. Right?

01:22.080 --> 01:24.750
Either way,
I'm gonna need a black dress.

01:24.750 --> 01:25.710
I'm fine.

01:25.710 --> 01:27.080
Diane, Jack, I'm fine.

01:27.080 --> 01:29.750
In fact, it's the best
I've felt in years.

01:29.750 --> 01:31.830
Well, congratulations,
Earl.

01:31.830 --> 01:32.960
Well, thank you,
Ruby.

01:32.960 --> 01:35.830
Mm. I had no idea
you would react that way.

01:35.830 --> 01:37.540
What are we, friends?

01:37.540 --> 01:38.920
Now, who is this girl

01:38.920 --> 01:42.750
whose life and credit
you're about to ruin?

01:42.750 --> 01:46.040
Her name is Lynette,
and I gotta tell y'all...

01:46.040 --> 01:48.790
[Inhales sharply]
she's the one.

01:48.790 --> 01:50.000
And how do you know?

01:50.000 --> 01:51.960
'Cause every time
I see her,

01:51.960 --> 01:55.790
Anita Baker's "Sweet Love"
plays in my head and my heart.

01:55.790 --> 01:58.620
Hmm. Do you also smell
burnt toast?

01:58.620 --> 02:00.540
Because that could be
a stroke.

02:00.540 --> 02:02.500
What's your con, old man?
Hmm?

02:02.500 --> 02:03.710
What is she?

02:03.710 --> 02:05.710
The heiress to Tommy Bahama
or something?

02:05.710 --> 02:07.000
[ Gasps ] Better yet,

02:07.000 --> 02:08.750
does she need
one of your kidneys?

02:08.750 --> 02:10.790
Better not.
Those kidneys are mine.

02:10.790 --> 02:12.960
It's the only thing I won
in the divorce.

02:12.960 --> 02:15.960
Thank you very much,
Johnnie Cochran and Associates.

02:15.960 --> 02:17.790
Huh.
I know
y'all got questions,

02:17.790 --> 02:19.580
but you'll just have to wait
'til you meet Lynette

02:19.580 --> 02:20.790
Friday at family dinner.

02:20.790 --> 02:22.620
Ruby: Mm.
[ Taps counter ]
Everybody be there.

02:22.620 --> 02:24.750
Excuse me.
I have to change.

02:24.750 --> 02:26.830
I'm late for something
called "tapas."

02:26.830 --> 02:27.960
[ Claps hands ]

02:27.960 --> 02:29.880
You know, it's great
that he's finally found love.

02:29.880 --> 02:32.750
What he found was
a 25-year-old yoga instructor

02:32.750 --> 02:35.670
with low self-esteem
whose name is Love.

02:35.670 --> 02:38.000
Dad, that's
the best-case scenario.

02:38.000 --> 02:40.500
It's probably one of those twins
Zoey hangs out with.

02:40.500 --> 02:41.500
[ Gasps ]

02:41.500 --> 02:42.790
Guys,
Pops will be Pops.

02:42.790 --> 02:45.580
All we have to do
is get through this dinner.

02:45.580 --> 02:46.460
Okay.
Oh.

02:46.460 --> 02:48.080
Baby.
Yeah?

02:48.080 --> 02:49.830
Can you make sure we have
some Martinelli's in the house

02:49.830 --> 02:51.920
just in case this girl
is too young to drink?

02:51.920 --> 02:52.880
Mm. She may not be
old enough,

02:52.880 --> 02:56.500
but if she's with Pops,
she drinks.

02:56.500 --> 02:59.460
[ Laughs ] Hey, Quavo.

02:59.460 --> 03:00.580
Yeah, I'm home.

03:00.580 --> 03:01.830
You know how I do.

03:01.830 --> 03:03.750
Keeping it juicy.
[ Laughs ]

03:03.750 --> 03:04.920
[ Refrigerator door closes ]

03:04.920 --> 03:06.830
[ Sighs ]
Oh, sorry, Quavo.

03:06.830 --> 03:08.960
Yeah, no, I'll catch you
on the flip side. See you later.

03:08.960 --> 03:11.880
Sorry, guys. That was
one-third of the Migos.

03:11.880 --> 03:13.000
The Quavo third.

03:13.000 --> 03:15.880
But can we go back to
how you're "keeping it juicy"?

03:15.880 --> 03:17.750
And then never
go back there again?

03:17.750 --> 03:18.880
[ Laughs ]

03:18.880 --> 03:21.000
I like you guys.
You keep me grounded.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.750
So, it has been
a hot minute.

03:23.750 --> 03:25.080
How are things going
in the real world?

03:25.080 --> 03:27.790
Well, uh,
here on Planet Earth,

03:27.790 --> 03:29.120
we make sure
people don't wear shirts

03:29.120 --> 03:31.580
that make them look like
the Kool-Aid Man.

03:31.580 --> 03:32.960
[ Chuckles ]

03:32.960 --> 03:36.620
Oh, you sweet,
stupid baby.

03:36.620 --> 03:37.960
Your little jabs --

03:37.960 --> 03:39.920
you know, they don't hurt
like they used to.

03:39.920 --> 03:41.580
You know you're talking
to Diane, right?

03:41.580 --> 03:43.120
I'm cool, Jack.

03:43.120 --> 03:44.170
You know,
hanging with rappers,

03:44.170 --> 03:45.750
it helps you to develop
a thick skin.

03:45.750 --> 03:47.790
Too bad your mustache
didn't get the memo, Longhead.

03:47.790 --> 03:50.540
See?
Don't even feel it.

03:50.540 --> 03:51.670
Shh.

03:51.670 --> 03:53.420
Gotta take this.

03:53.420 --> 03:54.460
[ Beep ]

03:54.460 --> 03:55.920
Hey. Cardi B!

03:55.920 --> 03:57.750
Yeah, Junior J. here.

03:57.750 --> 04:00.000
He is out of the house
one summer,

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
and he thinks
he can disrespect me?
Mnh-mnh.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.670
You got that Diane look like
you're about to do a murder.

04:04.670 --> 04:05.960
Go get my kit, Jack.

04:05.960 --> 04:07.880
I don't think
that seems --

04:07.880 --> 04:08.920
Get my kit!

04:08.920 --> 04:11.670
Oh. No need to...
say anything else.

04:11.670 --> 04:15.750
♪♪

04:15.750 --> 04:17.000
I hear your dad's
getting married,

04:17.000 --> 04:18.710
so I got him
two tickets to Disneyland

04:18.710 --> 04:20.170
for Star Wars:
Galaxy's Edge.

04:20.170 --> 04:23.920
Now, whether he takes me
or I take his fiancée --

04:23.920 --> 04:25.120
and it can happen
if I focus --

04:25.120 --> 04:27.000
someone's gonna be drinking
some blue milk.

04:27.000 --> 04:29.750
You're probably gonna have to
take somebody else, Charlie.

04:29.750 --> 04:31.540
I doubt
my father's getting married.

04:31.540 --> 04:32.210
Oh, no, Dre.

04:32.210 --> 04:35.170
I owe Jabba too many credits
to just be venturing alone

04:35.170 --> 04:37.580
in the wild frontiers
of Batuu.

04:37.580 --> 04:38.620
Hey, there he is!

04:38.620 --> 04:39.880
We, uh, we heard the news.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.880
Old Sex Factory Johnson

04:41.880 --> 04:43.960
snagged himself
a young bride, huh?
Mm-hmm.

04:43.960 --> 04:46.380
And with no money,
to an American woman.

04:46.380 --> 04:49.000
I mean,
the degree of difficulty...
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

04:49.000 --> 04:50.580
Wow!
Okay, guys...

04:50.580 --> 04:52.000
just calm down, alright?

04:52.000 --> 04:53.750
As soon as she drags him
to a Ty Dolla $ign concert,

04:53.750 --> 04:54.830
it's over.

04:54.830 --> 04:56.880
My pops is not
the marrying type, alright?

04:56.880 --> 04:58.040
He needs his freedom.

04:58.040 --> 04:59.040
People can change.

04:59.040 --> 05:00.080
Unh-unh.
Not my pops, man.

05:00.080 --> 05:01.880
Well, hey,
maybe your dad just needed

05:01.880 --> 05:03.170
the right circumstances
to change, right?

05:03.170 --> 05:06.040
L-Like after a breakup,
where she changes her number

05:06.040 --> 05:08.080
and...you change
your body weight.

05:08.080 --> 05:10.040
Stevens:
Change can be hard --

05:10.040 --> 05:11.960
unless we're talking
about climate change,

05:11.960 --> 05:14.080
which is not real,
okay?

05:14.080 --> 05:16.000
Summers are supposed to be
hot, everybody!

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
I knew a guy who wouldn't
change for anything.

05:18.000 --> 05:19.120
Unless he got angry.

05:19.120 --> 05:21.920
Then he'd rip his shirt off,
turn green,

05:21.920 --> 05:23.210
and wreck a city block.

05:23.210 --> 05:25.830
Charlie, are you talking
about the Incredible Hulk?

05:25.830 --> 05:27.000
Absolutely not.

05:27.000 --> 05:29.000
Talking about
this drunk Irish guy.

05:29.000 --> 05:30.040
Love Fitzy.

05:30.040 --> 05:31.830
See, you gotta have
your white friends, Dre.

05:31.830 --> 05:32.960
It's all about balance.

05:32.960 --> 05:35.000
I don't have to worry
about any of that, alright?

05:35.000 --> 05:37.080
Because the day
my dad changes

05:37.080 --> 05:39.750
is the day he starts
feeding the homeless.

05:39.750 --> 05:41.120
Outstanding, Dre.

05:41.120 --> 05:42.710
N-Now that we have solved
your problem,

05:42.710 --> 05:44.620
we can move on
to mine.

05:44.620 --> 05:46.790
Connor is in Iran.

05:46.790 --> 05:48.500
Not again.

05:48.500 --> 05:49.460
Oh.

05:49.460 --> 05:51.250
Those idiots could say
all they wanted,

05:51.250 --> 05:54.250
but after 45 years of life
with Earl Johnson,

05:54.250 --> 05:56.960
I know that man
better than he knows himself.

05:56.960 --> 05:59.960
[ Pops laughs ]

05:59.960 --> 06:03.710
Hey, Dre, Bow,
this is Lynette.

06:03.710 --> 06:04.830
Thi--

06:04.830 --> 06:06.540
Lynette!

06:06.540 --> 06:07.420
Hi!

06:07.420 --> 06:08.080
Isn't she lovely?

06:08.080 --> 06:09.460
Hold up, um...
Huh?

06:09.460 --> 06:12.250
[ Whispering ]
So, Lynette's mama
is also named Lynette?

06:12.250 --> 06:14.080
Okay, stop it, sweetie.
Oh, okay.

06:14.080 --> 06:17.000
Oh, it is so great
to finally meet you!
Oh --

06:17.000 --> 06:19.000
Look at this!
Okay!

06:19.000 --> 06:20.170
Alright. Oh!

06:20.170 --> 06:22.000
[ Anita Baker's "Sweet Love"
plays ]

06:22.000 --> 06:23.790
Oh, my goodness!

06:23.790 --> 06:24.880
I am so blessed.

06:24.880 --> 06:26.080
♪ Hear me
calling out your name ♪

06:26.080 --> 06:29.120
He hasn't kissed me
since "Motown 25"!

06:29.120 --> 06:31.620
What the [bleep]
is going on here?!

06:34.750 --> 06:37.080
As the night went on,
the surprises kept coming.

06:37.080 --> 06:39.170
There was Lynette,
Lynette's grown-man son Doug,

06:39.170 --> 06:41.830
and a Pops
I'd never seen before.

06:41.830 --> 06:44.000
He made her a plate.
Yes.

06:44.000 --> 06:45.000
You comfortable?
Mm-hmm.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.080
I have never seen that man

06:46.080 --> 06:48.170
put anything on a plate
for anybody.

06:48.170 --> 06:50.920
That is so sweet.

06:50.920 --> 06:52.080
Yeah,
you would think that.

06:52.080 --> 06:53.170
Oh, go away.

06:53.170 --> 06:57.170
So, Lynette, you know,
Pops has been real quiet

06:57.170 --> 07:00.170
about this whirlwind romance
you guys have.

07:00.170 --> 07:02.830
We don't know anything
about you.

07:02.830 --> 07:04.000
Like, zero.

07:04.000 --> 07:05.080
Do you have a job?

07:05.080 --> 07:07.580
Oh, Earl didn't say?

07:07.580 --> 07:08.620
No.

07:08.620 --> 07:11.500
I'm a judge
in the L.A. County Court system.

07:12.580 --> 07:14.000
A judge?

07:14.000 --> 07:14.920
Here, in our --
our home?

07:14.920 --> 07:17.290
Okay, uh, well,
will you excuse me?

07:17.290 --> 07:19.250
I need to dispose
of nothing.

07:19.250 --> 07:21.040
[ Footsteps departing rapidly ]

07:21.040 --> 07:23.080
I'm sorry --
I just can't get over the fact

07:23.080 --> 07:24.710
that you're engaged.

07:24.710 --> 07:25.380
Rainbow: Oh!

07:25.380 --> 07:27.000
Tell me --
how did you meet?

07:27.000 --> 07:28.120
Well, we met at a party,

07:28.120 --> 07:32.380
and Earl overheard me saying
that I had been divorced.

07:32.380 --> 07:36.380
And I said,
"So, you in the club?"

07:36.380 --> 07:39.290
Aah! That is exactly
the way he said it!

07:39.290 --> 07:40.540
Oh,
and we started talking,

07:40.540 --> 07:45.040
and I must have mentioned
going to this coffee shop.

07:45.040 --> 07:47.380
Then, one Monday,

07:47.380 --> 07:51.210
there was Earl,
reading the paper.

07:51.210 --> 07:52.210
No.
Mm-hmm.

07:52.210 --> 07:54.830
Then on Tuesday,
with the paper

07:54.830 --> 07:56.120
and my coffee.

07:56.120 --> 07:59.830
Then Wednesday,
and Thursday --

07:59.830 --> 08:01.290
And Friday, I said,

08:01.290 --> 08:03.710
"Girl, you ready
for something stronger?"

08:03.710 --> 08:05.210
[ Laughter ]

08:05.210 --> 08:07.750
We've been in love
ever since.

08:07.750 --> 08:09.000
That's so beautiful.

08:09.000 --> 08:10.170
Hold on.

08:10.170 --> 08:12.000
Man, you don't even
drink coffee.

08:12.000 --> 08:13.380
I don't.
[ Laughs ]

08:13.380 --> 08:16.000
Rainbow: Aww.
Good move, Pops.

08:16.000 --> 08:17.750
Everybody, hey-hey.

08:17.750 --> 08:19.040
Hey, Mama.

08:19.040 --> 08:20.120
Hey, Ruby.
Mm.

08:20.120 --> 08:21.670
This is Lynette.

08:22.210 --> 08:24.830
This woman right here?
This is Lynette?

08:24.830 --> 08:25.920
Yep.

08:27.040 --> 08:28.580
Uh-huh.

08:29.080 --> 08:31.960
The woman you're gonna marry?
This is her?

08:31.960 --> 08:33.670
That's me.
[ Chuckles lightly ]

08:37.000 --> 08:38.080
Look at you.

08:38.080 --> 08:39.250
Come here, girl.
Ohh!

08:39.250 --> 08:40.830
Come and give me a hug!

08:40.830 --> 08:41.670
Come on!

08:41.670 --> 08:43.170
[ Laughs ] There you go!
[ Laughs ] Oh.

08:43.170 --> 08:47.040
Let me guess --
you drink Sauvignon Blanc?

08:47.040 --> 08:48.290
Let me get you
a house pour.

08:48.290 --> 08:50.120
Okay.
[ Laughs ]

08:50.120 --> 08:52.040
That's so nice.
[ Chuckles lightly ]

08:52.040 --> 08:53.290
Well.

08:53.290 --> 08:55.540
You can just charm anybody,
can't you?

08:55.540 --> 08:58.040
I'm just trying
to keep up with you, Earl.

08:58.040 --> 08:59.120
[ Door thuds ]
[ Both laugh ]

08:59.120 --> 09:01.170
Um...I think we're okay.

09:01.170 --> 09:03.880
Just...don't let her
inside the garage.

09:03.880 --> 09:05.210
[ Exhales deeply ]

09:05.210 --> 09:07.920
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

09:08.960 --> 09:09.960
What?

09:09.960 --> 09:12.080
Well, that went
way too well.

09:12.080 --> 09:13.420
What are you up to,
Ruby?

09:13.420 --> 09:15.880
I'm genuinely happy
for Earl.

09:15.880 --> 09:16.920
Really?
Mm-hmm.

09:16.920 --> 09:19.710
I'm happy that old dog
is finally slowing down.

09:19.710 --> 09:20.540
Mm.

09:20.540 --> 09:22.710
Can't keep up with
them young women anymore.

09:22.710 --> 09:23.420
[ Chuckles ]

09:23.420 --> 09:27.000
Had to go find himself
a knock-off Ruby Johnson.

09:27.000 --> 09:28.250
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

09:28.250 --> 09:30.250
So you're really okay
that he's getting married?

09:30.250 --> 09:31.620
Please, Rainbow.

09:31.620 --> 09:34.330
I could have been married
four times over by now.

09:34.330 --> 09:36.250
Now, you know that,
right?
Okay.

09:36.250 --> 09:37.420
And let me tell you
something --

09:37.420 --> 09:40.120
Charles S. Dutton...
Uh-huh.

09:40.120 --> 09:42.880
...bought me
an above-ground hot tub.

09:42.880 --> 09:43.670
Okay?

09:43.670 --> 09:46.330
So, I am fine.

09:46.330 --> 09:47.330
Okay.
Lynette!

09:47.330 --> 09:49.170
Hey --
Got your wine, baby!

09:49.170 --> 09:50.250
Where --
H-Hey!

09:50.250 --> 09:51.420
Where -- Where is --
Here you go, baby!

09:51.420 --> 09:53.250
Where is the hot tub?
Wait --

09:53.250 --> 09:54.460
You know how he is.
I don't.

09:54.460 --> 09:57.080
So, then, Takeoff,
he says to me,

09:57.080 --> 09:59.500
"This is how you make it
in the rap game."

09:59.500 --> 10:01.330
Y-- You know what?
You know what?

10:01.330 --> 10:04.000
I...[Scoffs] I can't even
finish this story.

10:04.000 --> 10:05.380
I signed an NDA.

10:05.380 --> 10:08.210
But, uh, I can tell you
what happened...

10:08.210 --> 10:09.290
on a yacht.

10:09.290 --> 10:10.710
Okay.
Right?

10:10.710 --> 10:13.460
But again, I just asked if you
could point me to the bathroom.

10:13.460 --> 10:15.290
Oh! Right.
Uh, my apologizes.

10:15.290 --> 10:16.880
This way.

10:18.210 --> 10:19.500
Nah, this isn't right.

10:19.500 --> 10:21.330
If Junior had
a good yacht story --

10:21.330 --> 10:23.170
or if Junior had
any yacht story --

10:23.170 --> 10:24.880
he'd find a way
to spill it.

10:24.880 --> 10:25.540
Come on, Diane.

10:25.540 --> 10:27.290
Now that Junior's
signed to the NBA,

10:27.290 --> 10:28.380
we should be nice
to him.

10:28.380 --> 10:30.920
Maybe we can see the yacht
on his Instagram.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.710
Wait.

10:36.880 --> 10:37.620
Hold up.

10:37.620 --> 10:40.540
Look -- he's wearing
the same shirt in every post.

10:40.540 --> 10:43.380
There's no way he was hanging
out with the Migos all summer.

10:43.380 --> 10:46.040
Looks like Icarus
flew too close to the sun

10:46.040 --> 10:47.170
in his Gucci wool.

10:47.170 --> 10:49.290
You're right.
That's what I was thinking.

10:49.290 --> 10:50.420
That Icarus.

10:50.420 --> 10:52.080
I mean,
his album was fire --

10:52.080 --> 10:53.500
You don't have to know,
Jack.

10:53.500 --> 10:56.210
Got a call.
Sorry I was late.

10:56.210 --> 10:58.380
Quavo was pitching me
new interjections.

10:58.380 --> 11:01.250
He was starting
to feel "Unh!"

11:01.250 --> 11:03.380
But he was getting tired
of "Yuh!"

11:03.380 --> 11:06.000
You know, "Whoo!"
is kind of D.O.A.

11:06.000 --> 11:07.540
So...it's no big deal.

11:07.540 --> 11:10.500
Now that
we're all here, son,

11:10.500 --> 11:13.040
got something
I've been meaning to ask you.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.330
Ha! Here it comes.
What --

11:14.330 --> 11:16.420
Of course
you needed money.

11:16.420 --> 11:18.420
Finally, it's all starting
to come together.

11:18.420 --> 11:20.120
Here, take this hundred,
Pops.

11:20.120 --> 11:21.210
Hey, man,
just take the money.

11:21.210 --> 11:22.540
[ Chuckles ] Um...

11:22.540 --> 11:26.120
I was gonna ask you
if you'd be my best man.

11:26.120 --> 11:27.670
[ Gasps ] Oh!

11:29.080 --> 11:30.880
Oh.

11:31.830 --> 11:32.580
Uh...

11:32.580 --> 11:35.580
Yeah, sure,
I could...be your best man.

11:35.580 --> 11:38.460
Rainbow: Okay. Okay.
I got this. Alright.

11:38.460 --> 11:40.420
To the happy couple.

11:40.420 --> 11:45.040
If love were rocket fuel,
we could go to the moon.

11:45.040 --> 11:46.420
Ohh! [ Laughs ]

11:46.420 --> 11:48.670
Pops: Listen, y'all,
I just want everyone to know --

11:48.670 --> 11:51.330
I'm happier than I've ever been
in my entire life,

11:51.330 --> 11:55.880
and it's all down
to the love of a good woman.

11:56.420 --> 11:59.170
A good woman?

11:59.170 --> 12:01.380
Oh, hell no.

12:01.380 --> 12:03.210
[ Chuckling ] Okay.

12:03.210 --> 12:04.330
Uh-huh. Okay.

12:04.330 --> 12:06.420
♪♪

12:06.420 --> 12:07.670
[ Lynette and Pops humming ]

12:07.670 --> 12:10.170
Dre: Yeah, look at them.
Rainbow:
[ Chuckling ] What?

12:10.170 --> 12:12.250
He's drunk.
What?

12:12.250 --> 12:15.330
Dre, Pops asked you
to be his best man.

12:15.330 --> 12:17.330
That is what
you've always wanted.
I know.

12:17.330 --> 12:20.540
Every time you blow out
your birthday candles,

12:20.540 --> 12:22.500
that's exactly
what you're wishing for.

12:22.500 --> 12:23.710
That's exactly it.

12:23.710 --> 12:27.250
The man I know would have never
asked me to be his best man.

12:27.250 --> 12:28.250
Mm-hmm.

12:28.250 --> 12:29.670
[ Humming continues ]

12:29.670 --> 12:32.210
I don't even recognize
this guy.

12:32.210 --> 12:33.620
He's not
the settling-down type.

12:33.620 --> 12:35.710
Baby, he loves,
then leaves.

12:35.710 --> 12:38.380
The Pops I know
would never allow himself

12:38.380 --> 12:40.290
to be caught giggling.

12:40.290 --> 12:41.670
Hey,
what you staring at?

12:41.670 --> 12:44.250
You never seen
two people dancing together

12:44.250 --> 12:45.580
to music
that's not playing?

12:45.580 --> 12:47.330
You know,
this is crazy.

12:47.330 --> 12:49.330
I'm trying to find out
what your game is.

12:49.330 --> 12:51.500
Well, I'll tell you.
It's simple.

12:51.500 --> 12:55.120
I'm in love, sweet love,
Dummy.

12:55.120 --> 12:59.380
♪♪

12:59.380 --> 13:01.420
"A good woman."

13:01.420 --> 13:03.120
[ Chuckles ]

13:03.120 --> 13:04.120
Hey.

13:04.120 --> 13:05.120
Unh.

13:06.330 --> 13:08.330
Okay. [ Chuckles ]

13:08.330 --> 13:09.460
Yo.
[ Chuckles ]

13:09.460 --> 13:13.120
Is it me, or is this all
kind of out of nowhere?

13:13.120 --> 13:13.790
Exactly.

13:13.790 --> 13:16.250
And how is it that we're
the only two that notice this?

13:16.250 --> 13:17.380
I don't know!

13:17.380 --> 13:18.750
[ Both laughing ]

13:18.750 --> 13:21.460
I mean, they barely
know each other.

13:21.460 --> 13:22.670
And they're so different.

13:22.670 --> 13:24.460
Yeah.
I mean,
my mom's a judge.

13:24.460 --> 13:26.170
My pops is not.
[ Chuckles ]

13:26.170 --> 13:27.380
No, he isn't.
Uh-huh.

13:27.380 --> 13:28.670
Oh, we all know
his type.

13:28.670 --> 13:30.620
60s, never really
settled down...

13:30.620 --> 13:32.540
Oh, he has never
settled down.

13:32.540 --> 13:34.380
...rolling stone...
Oh.

13:34.380 --> 13:35.620
...going where the wind
takes him...

13:35.620 --> 13:37.620
Oh, and the wind
is blowing.

13:37.620 --> 13:39.290
...probably running
a credit scam,

13:39.290 --> 13:40.670
has multiple IDs,

13:40.670 --> 13:42.670
always has a bag
packed in the trunk...

13:42.670 --> 13:44.670
Uh, I mean, you know, who don't
have a bag packed in the trunk?

13:44.670 --> 13:46.420
...first-name basis
at the strip club

13:46.420 --> 13:47.580
and the track...

13:47.580 --> 13:49.580
Well, the track. But, you know,
he don't really throw money --

13:49.580 --> 13:51.380
...new girl on his arm
every single night.

13:51.380 --> 13:52.500
Mm. Never faithful.

13:52.500 --> 13:54.420
Well, hey, hey.
Hey, hold on, man.

13:54.420 --> 13:56.420
He's faithful to your mama,
alright?

13:56.420 --> 13:57.500
Dude is in love.

13:57.500 --> 14:00.420
Hey, bruh...
he fixed her a plate.

14:00.420 --> 14:02.540
Oh, so I'm supposed to ignore
all that other stuff

14:02.540 --> 14:04.670
because he put some olives
on a plate?

14:04.670 --> 14:06.620
There were also meats,
Doug.

14:06.620 --> 14:09.250
What is your problem, man?
He's changed.

14:09.250 --> 14:10.380
Sure he has.

14:10.380 --> 14:12.120
No. He has.

14:12.710 --> 14:16.170
He's dipping your mother
to music only they can hear.

14:16.170 --> 14:17.710
He's giggling.

14:17.710 --> 14:21.330
He's saying nice stuff about me
in front of my family.

14:21.330 --> 14:22.540
Bruh, he's changed.

14:22.540 --> 14:24.620
Whatever.

14:24.620 --> 14:27.040
I don't think
you hear me, man.

14:28.120 --> 14:30.040
He's changed.

14:31.540 --> 14:33.580
Look, man...

14:33.580 --> 14:35.670
I'm not gonna be talked to
like that.

14:35.670 --> 14:38.460
I talk how I wanna talk
in my house, Doug.

14:38.460 --> 14:40.580
Because my pops
has changed.

14:40.580 --> 14:41.790
Oh, he's changed, huh?
Yes, he's changed.

14:41.790 --> 14:43.710
Oh, he's changed, huh?
He's changed!

14:43.710 --> 14:44.880
Rainbow:
Hey! Hey, hey, hey!
Changed, huh?
Yeah!

14:44.880 --> 14:46.960
Pops: Hey!
My father has changed!
He's changed? Changed?

14:46.960 --> 14:49.540
What's going on?!
That's enough of that, now!
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey!

14:49.540 --> 14:50.620
He's changed!
Doug:
Oh, he's changed, huh?

14:50.620 --> 14:53.330
Order! Order!
Order in the dining room!

14:54.330 --> 14:55.880
Yes, Your Honor.

14:59.250 --> 15:02.000
My pops has changed.

15:03.420 --> 15:05.460
I'm sorry about these boys,
Lynette.

15:05.460 --> 15:06.710
Guess next time,
we'll just have to

15:06.710 --> 15:08.500
get the boxing gear
out of the garage.

15:08.500 --> 15:11.080
[ Gasps ]
Stay out of the garage!

15:12.500 --> 15:13.500
It's a mess in there.

15:13.500 --> 15:15.000
♪♪

15:18.210 --> 15:19.290
Hey.
Mm?

15:19.290 --> 15:21.420
Hey. What was that?

15:21.420 --> 15:22.670
I haven't seen
that version of Dre

15:22.670 --> 15:24.750
since you got banned
from Little League.

15:24.750 --> 15:27.170
You need to go
apologize.

15:27.170 --> 15:28.580
I can't admit fault.

15:28.580 --> 15:30.380
What?
Lynette's a judge.

15:30.380 --> 15:31.750
Anything I say
in front of her

15:31.750 --> 15:34.580
can and will be used against me
in a court of law.

15:34.580 --> 15:35.710
That's not
how this works, Dre.

15:35.710 --> 15:37.790
Oh, so, what?
Are you a lawyer now, too?

15:37.790 --> 15:38.750
Could've been.

15:38.750 --> 15:39.790
He started it.
He --

15:39.790 --> 15:41.790
He was acting
as if Pops was a deadbeat!

15:41.790 --> 15:45.620
Dre, you call your dad
a deadbeat all the time.

15:45.620 --> 15:47.790
That's how you labeled
his Netflix profile.

15:47.790 --> 15:50.620
Because he was a deadbeat.

15:50.620 --> 15:51.880
That's all I knew
my whole life,

15:51.880 --> 15:54.580
a-a-and now
he's turned into this guy?

15:54.580 --> 15:56.210
Isn't that a good thing?

15:56.210 --> 15:56.960
No!

15:56.960 --> 15:59.620
I always thought
Pops did the best he could.

15:59.620 --> 16:02.580
Now it turns out
he could have did better.

16:02.580 --> 16:04.580
He just decided not to.

16:04.580 --> 16:06.750
And I don't get why.

16:06.750 --> 16:09.960
Just talk to your dad.

16:11.290 --> 16:12.210
Okay.

16:12.210 --> 16:15.580
♪♪

16:15.580 --> 16:17.710
On my time.

16:17.710 --> 16:19.710
If that's what I decide.

16:19.710 --> 16:21.210
But not because of you.

16:21.210 --> 16:21.880
Okay.

16:21.880 --> 16:23.580
I had that idea
on my own.

16:23.580 --> 16:24.620
'Course you did.

16:24.620 --> 16:26.000
♪♪

16:26.000 --> 16:29.500
So, "Walk It Talk It"
is a great encore, Quavo,

16:29.500 --> 16:30.830
but "Stir Fry" --
that is --

16:30.830 --> 16:31.880
Oh, my God.
Is that Quavo?

16:31.880 --> 16:33.580
Put him on speaker.
I want to say hi.

16:33.580 --> 16:35.330
Oh, uh...
[Chuckles] can't.

16:35.330 --> 16:36.500
You know, uh...

16:36.500 --> 16:38.620
confidential rap stuff,
secret lyrics --

16:38.620 --> 16:40.880
codes,
you know, remixes.

16:40.880 --> 16:41.880
Ohhh.
You guys get it.
[ Chuckles ]

16:41.880 --> 16:42.920
I get it. Understood.
Yeah.

16:42.920 --> 16:44.620
You got to keep it
professional, so...

16:44.620 --> 16:45.580
Yeah, yeah.
Uh-huh.

16:45.580 --> 16:46.750
[ Clicks tongue ]

16:46.750 --> 16:49.580
So, Quavious,
as I was saying, my --

16:49.580 --> 16:50.670
[ Cellphone beeps ]

16:50.670 --> 16:52.500
Female voice:
The affirmation hotline --

16:52.500 --> 16:54.620
all good, all the time,

16:54.620 --> 16:55.620
just like you.

16:55.620 --> 16:56.620
[ Cellphone beeps ]

16:56.620 --> 16:57.880
What gave me away?

16:57.880 --> 17:00.620
You wore the same shirt
in every post.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.460
Like a real Icarus.

17:02.460 --> 17:04.500
So, Junior...

17:04.500 --> 17:07.460
looks like
I got you over a barrel.

17:07.460 --> 17:09.540
Any last words?

17:09.540 --> 17:11.670
Okay, guys, Migos brought me on
for one tour,

17:11.670 --> 17:13.710
and it turns out
it was a really short tour,

17:13.710 --> 17:15.960
and I made this big deal
about going out on my own,

17:15.960 --> 17:18.580
but when things went bad, I
didn't know how to tell anybody,

17:18.580 --> 17:19.710
and I bought
all this Bitcoin,

17:19.710 --> 17:21.670
and, Diane,
please, don't tell Mom.

17:21.670 --> 17:22.710
[ Chuckles ]

17:22.710 --> 17:26.540
Oh, you sweet,
stupid baby.

17:26.540 --> 17:28.710
Unlike you,
I don't lie to live.

17:28.710 --> 17:30.500
I lie for fun.

17:30.500 --> 17:31.750
And besides,
your sad spin-out

17:31.750 --> 17:33.580
was the lamest thing
I've ever seen.

17:33.580 --> 17:34.750
You're no threat to me.

17:34.750 --> 17:37.500
And you should be able
to tell Mom about your job

17:37.500 --> 17:38.710
when you're ready.

17:38.710 --> 17:40.380
Diane, thank you --

17:40.380 --> 17:41.380
Oh, yeah, she not done.

17:41.380 --> 17:42.620
Now, we can agree

17:42.620 --> 17:43.920
that I've done
something for you,

17:43.920 --> 17:45.920
and one day, I'll ask you
to do something for me.

17:45.920 --> 17:47.750
When the time comes,
you'll know.

17:47.750 --> 17:49.580
You'll want to renew
your passport.

17:49.580 --> 17:54.750
♪♪

17:54.750 --> 17:58.330
[ Breathes deeply ]

18:00.460 --> 18:02.670
So, Pops...

18:02.670 --> 18:04.750
[ Smacks lips ]

18:04.750 --> 18:06.920
...I think
I like Lynette.

18:06.920 --> 18:09.540
You know, if she becomes
a TV judge,

18:09.540 --> 18:10.580
I'd watch.

18:10.580 --> 18:11.830
truTV keeps asking.
Hmm.

18:11.830 --> 18:13.580
But she's way too classy
for that.

18:13.580 --> 18:14.580
[ Chuckles ]

18:14.580 --> 18:16.080
But, see, what --
Mm.

18:16.080 --> 18:19.830
...what I can't wrap
my head around, Pops, is...

18:19.830 --> 18:22.620
why does she get
the best Earl Johnson?

18:23.290 --> 18:26.710
How come you couldn't give that
to me when I needed it, Pops?

18:26.710 --> 18:28.420
Oh.

18:29.790 --> 18:30.790
I don't know.

18:30.790 --> 18:32.750
Uh...probably 'cause
I didn't know how,

18:32.750 --> 18:35.580
and it wasn't like
I had anybody to show me.

18:36.620 --> 18:38.620
This woman
makes me feel different.

18:38.620 --> 18:41.540
I mean, I feel younger,
less grumpy.

18:41.540 --> 18:43.120
I-I-I'm way more thoughtful.

18:43.120 --> 18:45.960
Hell, I'm not even stealing bags
out the airport anymore,

18:45.960 --> 18:48.790
and that's where I found
the engagement ring.

18:48.790 --> 18:50.790
Not even Burbank?

18:50.790 --> 18:53.500
As an officer of the court, she
frowns on that kind of thing,

18:53.500 --> 18:55.460
so no go.

18:55.460 --> 18:57.620
Look, I get it --

18:57.620 --> 18:59.120
it's a lot,
especially for you.

18:59.120 --> 19:01.580
Got to be a lot
to see me change like this.

19:01.580 --> 19:03.500
But I can't help it, son.
I'm in love.

19:04.000 --> 19:06.460
I'm not asking you
to be happy for me.

19:06.460 --> 19:08.210
I'm not. I'm just...

19:09.000 --> 19:11.580
I am asking you
to be happy with me.

19:13.420 --> 19:14.670
[ Chuckles lightly ]

19:14.670 --> 19:16.920
Yeah, man, I...

19:16.920 --> 19:19.540
I can be happy with you.

19:19.540 --> 19:20.540
Okay.

19:21.540 --> 19:22.710
Congrats, Pops.

19:22.710 --> 19:24.000
Thank you, son.
Thank you.

19:24.000 --> 19:26.620
And I am honored
to be your best man.

19:26.620 --> 19:27.790
[ Scoffs ]
Honored to have you.

19:27.790 --> 19:28.960
Okay.
Now, look.

19:28.960 --> 19:31.830
W-We need to talk about
the bachelor party.

19:31.830 --> 19:32.960
Okay,
yeah, yeah, yeah, man.

19:32.960 --> 19:34.830
Are we gonna go strip club
or the racetrack?

19:34.830 --> 19:36.670
Or we can have strip club
at the racetrack.

19:36.670 --> 19:37.750
[ Both chuckle ]

19:37.750 --> 19:39.750
Wait, wait, you --
you wanted to come?

19:39.750 --> 19:42.620
Uh, look, let me just run it
by my man Loose Craig

19:42.620 --> 19:43.670
right quick.

19:43.670 --> 19:45.710
I just don't want
to get your hopes up, son.

19:45.710 --> 19:46.750
Just hold that thought.

19:46.750 --> 19:48.330
You my man, Dre.

19:48.880 --> 19:50.620
You my best man.

19:54.330 --> 19:55.290
[ Screams ]

19:56.460 --> 19:57.920
Diane. You okay?

19:57.920 --> 20:00.380
I had a dream
about chaos.

20:00.380 --> 20:01.620
Oh.

20:01.620 --> 20:02.710
That's nice.

20:02.710 --> 20:03.880
No.

20:03.880 --> 20:05.620
This time,
it was a nightmare.

20:05.620 --> 20:07.880
The world was...
upside down.

20:07.880 --> 20:09.920
The ocean, the sky,
the land --

20:09.920 --> 20:13.670
they were all jumbled,
and...there was no light.

20:13.670 --> 20:14.670
Only darkness.

20:14.670 --> 20:17.210
There was no Mom or Dad.

20:17.210 --> 20:20.380
Zoey was a loser,
and Junior was a success.

20:20.380 --> 20:21.710
Whoa.

20:21.710 --> 20:23.040
That does sound
disturbing.

20:23.040 --> 20:26.040
You and I were all alone,

20:26.040 --> 20:28.920
tumbling
through the universe.

20:28.920 --> 20:31.710
I was holding your hand,
but I could --

20:31.710 --> 20:33.750
I could feel you
slipping away.

20:33.750 --> 20:37.580
♪♪

20:37.580 --> 20:38.620
Diane...

20:38.620 --> 20:40.540
it's okay.

20:40.540 --> 20:41.620
It's just a dream.

20:41.620 --> 20:42.880
You're home, safe.

20:42.880 --> 20:44.920
You'll always have me.

20:44.920 --> 20:47.000
And even if we're not
holding hands,

20:47.000 --> 20:48.790
we're always connected.

20:48.790 --> 20:50.750
♪♪

20:50.750 --> 20:51.830
Thanks, friend.

20:51.830 --> 20:53.120
♪♪

20:53.120 --> 20:55.580
Wanna get
some ice cream?

20:55.580 --> 20:56.710
Yeah.

20:56.710 --> 20:58.500
If Dad left us any.

20:58.500 --> 20:59.500
[ Chuckles ]

20:59.500 --> 21:00.540
[ Sniffles ]

21:00.540 --> 21:02.670
[ Sighs ]

21:02.670 --> 21:11.380
♪♪

21:11.380 --> 21:13.920
-Mom!
-Shh! Daddy's working!

21:16.920 --> 21:17.920
♪♪
